EEG Language Study

rr library(readr) library(dplyr) library(ggplot2) library(ez)

Behavioral Data Analysis

Begin by loading the behavioral data.

rr behavioral.data<- read_csv(‘Data/behavioral_data_tidy.csv’)

Adding a percent correct calculation, means and SD

rr behavioral.data <- behavioral.data %>% mutate(PercentCorrect = CorrectResponses / 29*100) behavioral.data %>% group_by(Condition) %>% summarize(M= mean(PercentCorrect), SD= sd(PercentCorrect))

Are people more accurate with anamalous sentences than literal sentences?

rr t.test(PercentCorrect ~ Condition, data =behavioral.data %>% filter(Condition %in% c(, )), paired = TRUE)

Are people better at literal than metaphorical?

rr t.test(PercentCorrect ~ Condition, data =behavioral.data %>% filter(Condition %in% c(, )), paired = TRUE)

Visualize the behavioral data with a boxplot

rr ggplot(behavioral.data, aes(x=Condition, y=PercentCorrect))+geom_violin() + geom_jitter()
